Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.28,0:01:45.20,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,Do you remember the first time we met, Kimblee?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.20,0:01:47.08,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,It seems our positions are now reversed!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.41,0:01:49.25,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you dare look down on me!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.25,0:01:55.17,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Kimblee, you bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.92,0:01:59.93,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Why... Why is Winry here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.93,0:02:03.51,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,We were just about to capture Scar, but now he's taken her hostage!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.51,0:02:05.14,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Move.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.89,0:02:09.98,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.56,0:02:14.36,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Stop, Crimson Alchemist!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.82,0:02:17.44,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Do you not see Winry in front of you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.91,0:02:23.08,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Don't get in my way!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.38,0:02:35.09,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Hold it, Scar!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.09,0:02:38.34,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Kimblee, don't go near the building! It's dangerous!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.88,0:02:41.55,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Withdraw!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.18,0:02:44.30,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,There's a blizzard approaching! Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.40,0:02:53.15,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,You're a fantastic actor.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.44,0:02:55.07,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,That wasn't an act.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.86,0:03:02.57,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I'm actually furious at myself for being such a coward and having to put up such an act.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.16,0:03:08.70,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you kill my parents? {ep38}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.25,0:03:12.96,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,No matter what I say, it'll be only an excuse. {ep38}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.67,0:03:17.75,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,The fact is I killed the Rockbells. {ep38}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.13,0:03:19.21,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,With this hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.35,0:03:30.73,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,Girl, you have the right to kill me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.78,0:03:45.82,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,At this rate, you'll die from blood loss.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.82,0:03:47.08,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Winry!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.08,0:03:47.99,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.33,0:03:52.50,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm sure Mom and Dad would have done the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.63,0:03:58.25,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,It's a life Mom and Dad saved.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.96,0:04:00.92,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure there's a meaning to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.01,0:04:04.22,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,You're saying you'll forgive me?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.22,0:04:08.22,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Don't get the wrong idea! I haven't forgiven you for killing my parents unjustly!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.15,0:04:20.98,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Winry...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.24,0:04:24.57,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry; I'm not going to cry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.53,0:04:30.91,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't I promise you that the next time I cry, it'd be with tears of joy?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.92,0:04:41.38,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Scar.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.01,0:04:51.01,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Despite what Winry just said, I still want to beat you to a pulp and drag you over to the Rockbells' graves.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.10,0:04:57.85,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Should I contact Headquarters?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.85,0:04:58.52,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.86,0:05:01.02,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,I believe Miles was your name?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.32,0:05:03.86,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,Can I ask something?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.24,0:05:05.28,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.41,0:05:08.78,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,You called me a fellow countryman, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.41,0:05:10.28,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.58,0:05:13.00,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Until my grandfather's generation, my ancestors were full Ishbalans.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.12,0:05:19.38,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,I wish we could have met under different circumstances, my red-eyed brethren.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.21,0:05:24.17,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you siding with the Amestrian army?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.34,0:05:32.85,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Because I wish to change the way people feel about Ishbalans from within the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.18,0:05:39.60,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt people would change the way they feel so easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.23,0:05:43.36,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know how long it'll take.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.07,0:05:47.86,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,But there are things only I,\Na man of mixed parentage, can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.78,0:05:52.91,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,I'm nothing but an Ishbalan pebble that was thrown into the Amestrian army.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.41,0:05:57.96,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,But there may come a time when\Na small ripple becomes a giant wave.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.33,0:06:07.38,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,And ironically, the person who made me realize that is a full-blooded Amestrian.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.47,0:06:16.31,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,I'm nothing but a mass of hatred, born from that civil war.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.52,0:06:21.27,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad someone like you exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.65,0:06:24.48,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Major.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.74,0:06:28.70,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Is this Headquarters?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.70,0:06:30.16,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,This is Miles speaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.82,0:06:33.08,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,We've captured Scar in a building in Area D.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.53,0:06:35.41,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Let Kimblee know.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.29,0:06:43.29,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,No matter what your circumstances are,\NI can't just let you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.88,0:06:45.92,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,You deserve to be tried and sentenced.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.92,0:06:47.09,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.59,0:06:48.30,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.59,0:06:50.47,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,May!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.55,0:06:52.76,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Doctor Marcoh!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.35,0:06:56.31,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't take that man away.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.27,0:07:03.31,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,This is bad, Sir Kimblee.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.69,0:07:07.07,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,The clouds are moving fast.\NThe weather's about to get pretty ugly.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.65,0:07:10.90,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Then let's hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.28,0:07:13.82,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Deciphering research documents?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.41,0:07:20.33,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,It's breakthrough research that combines the alchemies from Amestris and Xing!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.75,0:07:24.96,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,But the essential portions are written in ancient Ishbalan.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.67,0:07:28.30,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,The only one who can read this is Scar.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.30,0:07:29.26,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.34,0:07:34.22,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,You're the girl who knows Eastern Alchemy, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.80,0:07:37.81,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,I've received orders to take you back to the fort.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.81,0:07:39.81,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?! M-Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.27,0:07:41.39,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.77,0:07:43.73,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,I've been ordered to give you a warm reception.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.10,0:07:47.40,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Now... if Scar can't be caught...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.90,0:07:51.61,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,...and if we also can't let them know that Marcoh is here...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.07,0:07:57.78,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,It might be better to just hide them at Briggs for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.78,0:08:00.66,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Hang on, what the hell?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.66,0:08:02.75,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,You're taking {\i1}him{\i0}, too?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.46,0:08:06.13,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you guys need him to decipher the documents?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.84,0:08:09.21,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It pisses me off to think we have to ask {\i1}him{\i0\fscx30} {\r} for help...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.21,0:08:11.72,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't we just hand him over to Kimblee and-
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.21,0:08:12.63,Default-alt,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,A transmutation circle made from this country.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.97,0:08:16.30,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,And the history of this country.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.80,0:08:19.14,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,I've heard everything from General Armstrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.85,0:08:23.73,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Something is about to happen;\Nsomething that will encompass all of Amestris.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.48,0:08:28.82,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't deciphering the documents of higher priority than anything else?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.90,0:08:34.57,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,I'm also aware that Ms. Rockbell has been taken hostage.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.24,0:08:39.62,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,If we do this now, we could make Kimblee take the blame and hide her away at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.21,0:08:50.96,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Scar, if you decide to lend us a hand,\Nwe can postpone your trial to a later date.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.51,0:08:52.26,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,What do you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.59,0:08:56.38,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,I have no other options, do I?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.22,0:08:59.01,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,I promise to cooperate.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.35,0:09:01.89,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Do you really mean it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.64,0:09:07.40,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,I swear on my Ishbalan blood, my red-eyed brethren.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.52,0:09:09.81,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,So, that's how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.36,0:09:14.65,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, but you're going to have to wait a little longer for him to face trial.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.74,0:09:16.32,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,That's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.78,0:09:21.58,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Oh yeah, I forgot about these two.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.91,0:09:22.66,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Kill them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.66,0:09:23.37,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.37,0:09:24.58,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.58,0:09:27.67,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Hang on! You don't have to kill them!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.67,0:09:29.75,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,There's nothing to be gained from letting them live.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.75,0:09:30.29,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.29,0:09:34.92,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't about gain or loss! Isn't there something you could do besides killing them?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.97,0:09:38.59,Default,Jel,0000,0000,0000,,Showing us pity, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.59,0:09:42.14,Default,Zan,0000,0000,0000,,There's no need for that. You're just a kid who doesn't know anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.64,0:09:45.81,Default,Jel,0000,0000,0000,,There's no future for us anyway, since we've got bodies like these.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.81,0:09:47.60,Default,Jel,0000,0000,0000,,If you're going to kill us, just do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.23,0:09:52.94,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you two have family or people important to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.94,0:09:54.23,Default,Jel,0000,0000,0000,,Of course we do.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.65,0:09:58.36,Default,Zan,0000,0000,0000,,But when we were transformed to this state, we were publicly pronounced dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.91,0:10:00.07,Default,Zan,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't seen them since.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.62,0:10:02.45,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you {\i1}want{\i0\fscx30} {\r} to see them?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.45,0:10:05.83,Default,Zan,0000,0000,0000,,Even if we did, there's nothing we could do. Look at us.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.71,0:10:11.54,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, so you don't want to return to your old selves?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.54,0:10:14.25,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,You're fine with those bodies, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.25,0:10:15.51,Default,Zan,0000,0000,0000,,Of course not!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.51,0:10:17.59,Default,Jan,0000,0000,0000,,Of course we want to return to normal!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.63,0:10:20.14,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Then there's your answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.30,0:10:25.02,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't talk as though you've already given up.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.02,0:10:28.98,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,You haven't even explored the possibility of returning to your old bodies.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.69,0:10:33.15,Default,Jan,0000,0000,0000,,How the hell would {\i1}you{\i0\fscx30} {\r} know how we feel?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.15,0:10:35.19,Default,Zan,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way to-
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.91,0:10:42.37,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to get my body back.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.74,0:10:46.37,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how many years it may take, I'll never give up!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.33,0:10:49.29,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Major!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.83,0:10:51.71,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.71,0:10:52.42,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't good.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.92,0:10:54.17,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,A blizzard is approaching.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.84,0:10:57.92,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,It's impossible to march in a blizzard with the equipment we have right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.51,0:11:00.93,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,At this rate, we won't make it back to the fort.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.97,0:11:03.18,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,What should we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.55,0:11:05.81,Default,Yoki,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't this a mining town?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.81,0:11:08.18,Default,Yoki,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't we just take the underground mining path?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.85,0:11:11.39,Default,Yoki,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.81,0:11:17.90,Default,Yoki,0000,0000,0000,,I-It's just that since this is such a big mine, I figured there might be a path leading through the mountain...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.07,0:11:20.74,Default,Yoki,0000,0000,0000,,I-I think...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.20,0:11:21.28,Default-alt,Both,0000,0000,0000,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.74,0:11:22.32,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Yoki!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.32,0:11:25.03,Default,Yoki,0000,0000,0000,,I used to own a coal mine, after all!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.83,0:11:28.79,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,That would work! The mine exits beyond the mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.79,0:11:29.83,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.37,0:11:33.71,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,If you happen to encounter a soldier from Briggs, hand them this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.71,0:11:38.51,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,I've stated the situation in there, so they should give you refuge.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.51,0:11:39.76,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,I'm in your debt.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.97,0:11:43.72,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,I guess the only thing we still have to account for is the girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.64,0:11:53.27,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,Even if she comes with us, wouldn't the Elric Brothers be the prime suspects if they find out she's missing?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.19,0:11:55.52,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,We'll figure something out.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.52,0:11:59.23,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Don't mean to brag, but we can work as well as we can talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.23,0:12:02.95,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,No, Kimblee is a very suspicious man.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.36,0:12:06.16,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,If we don't plan this completely, he'll be doubly suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.58,0:12:17.21,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Umm... this may be a bit strange coming from me...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.88,0:12:19.13,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.55,0:12:24.01,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,What if I were kidnapped by Scar?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.06,0:12:32.77,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,"Kidnapped"?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.23,0:12:35.06,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,So... what you mean is...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.48,0:12:38.15,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,We free him, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.15,0:12:46.32,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Scar runs off with me in his arms, and you pretend like you're desperately trying to stop him...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.99,0:12:47.78,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,...or something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.78,0:12:50.24,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think we'll let you do something that dangerous?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.45,0:12:51.41,Default-alt,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a hostage right now, anyway!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.79,0:12:55.25,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,I have to risk my life to escape, or it'll never happen!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.25,0:12:57.38,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,But with Scar?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.38,0:13:00.88,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! You don't need to risk {\i1}your{\i0\fscx30} {\r} life!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.05,0:13:05.55,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Quit trying to do everything by yourselves! I'm tired of it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.55,0:13:12.18,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry up and decide. The blizzard is coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.72,0:13:15.31,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Pretty soon, we won't even be able to leave this building.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.57,0:13:22.07,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Kimblee's squad is here!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.45,0:13:27.24,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.61,0:13:30.70,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Scar, if anything happens...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.70,0:13:33.58,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,I know. I plan to keep my promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.29,0:13:39.29,Default,Jel,0000,0000,0000,,Could you...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.04,0:13:42.80,Default,Jel,0000,0000,0000,,Could you take us, as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.17,0:13:46.55,Default,Jel,0000,0000,0000,,I understand you don't trust us,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.55,0:13:49.68,Default,Jel,0000,0000,0000,,so you can keep us bound.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.35,0:13:53.72,Default,Zam,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Kimblee shows no mercy to men who can't do their job.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.72,0:13:55.64,Default,Zam,0000,0000,0000,,We'll get killed either way.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.64,0:13:56.56,Default,Zam,0000,0000,0000,,And besides...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.14,0:13:59.15,Default,Zam,0000,0000,0000,,...we don't want to give up, either!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.90,0:14:03.44,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,We can trust you, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.90,0:14:10.53,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,If you two happen to betray us and get in our way, this country could fall to ruin.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.91,0:14:13.70,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,Including the people you two hold dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.58,0:14:16.70,Default,Jel,0000,0000,0000,,Hang on! What do you mean?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.25,0:14:20.38,Default,Jel,0000,0000,0000,,Central never told us anything like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.38,0:14:23.25,Default,Zam,0000,0000,0000,,Tell us the details! What is this about?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.34,0:14:32.55,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Is this fine?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.30,0:14:36.64,Default,Jel,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. You all will probably feel safer this way, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.81,0:14:40.44,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Scar, we're going to have to ask you to put on an act.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.02,0:14:42.44,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.44,0:14:46.69,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Keep the vow you swore on your Ishbalan blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.82,0:14:55.12,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! You need to take off your earrings!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.54,0:14:58.25,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Those are made out of metal, aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.62,0:15:00.75,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't take them off, you'll get frostbite.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.26,0:15:10.05,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Ed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.14,0:15:13.76,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on to these for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.22,0:15:17.68,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be waiting for you at the fort!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.74,0:15:30.70,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Kimblee, you bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.70,0:15:33.78,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Why the hell didn't you keep an eye on Winry?! {ep38}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.92,0:15:51.72,Default,Hein,0000,0000,0000,,I'm worried about Zampano and Jerso.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.13,0:15:55.97,Default,Dar,0000,0000,0000,,They were either killed by Scar, or they can't move because of the blizzard...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.97,0:15:58.47,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Scar shouldn't be able to move, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.47,0:16:01.06,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,He has to be in this town somewhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.06,0:16:04.23,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,We ought to plan our next search while we're sitting here!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.36,0:16:08.78,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,This blizzard really saved us...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.53,0:16:12.15,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,I pray that all of you will make it to the fort.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.28,0:16:16.32,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Major Miles, you have a phone call from Briggs.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.08,0:16:20.95,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Miles speaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.92,0:16:24.79,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.55,0:16:33.55,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, so you're the daughter of those Rockbells.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.13,0:16:36.30,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,You've heard of my parents?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.30,0:16:41.81,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,There isn't a single doctor who was in Ishbal who hasn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.27,0:16:45.81,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,They fulfilled their duties as doctors without any regard for their own lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.15,0:16:50.73,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't forgiven that you killed my parents unjustly!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.61,0:16:55.07,Default,Man,0000,0000,0000,,You must endure.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.07,0:16:58.37,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,So you're telling me to forgive the army for what they did?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.37,0:17:00.74,Default,Man,0000,0000,0000,,"Enduring" and "forgiving" are two different things.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.74,0:17:03.37,Default,Man,0000,0000,0000,,You must not forgive the unjustness of society.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.37,0:17:05.96,Default,Man,0000,0000,0000,,As a human being, you must hold the event in contempt.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.96,0:17:08.88,Default,Man,0000,0000,0000,,Yet, you must endure.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.88,0:17:12.17,Default,Man,0000,0000,0000,,You must put an end to the chain of hatred!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.46,0:17:17.09,Default,Bro,0000,0000,0000,,If many negative emotions gather,\Nthey will end up influencing the entire world.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.64,0:17:22.68,Default,Bro,0000,0000,0000,,But on the other hand, it is also possible to gather positive emotions and lead the world in that direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.93,0:17:27.69,Default,Bro,0000,0000,0000,,That is why I study alchemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.61,0:17:33.53,Default,Yoki,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, here we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.19,0:17:35.82,Default,Zam,0000,0000,0000,,What is this place?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.40,0:17:38.66,Default,Yoki,0000,0000,0000,,It's a post for mine officers.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.66,0:17:39.78,Default,Yoki,0000,0000,0000,,There should be...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.78,0:17:41.37,Default,Yoki,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, found it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.37,0:17:44.45,Default,Yoki,0000,0000,0000,,See? A detailed map of the mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.91,0:17:46.46,Default,Jer,0000,0000,0000,,It looks pretty complicated.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.46,0:17:48.46,Default,Jer,0000,0000,0000,,I don't understand what goes where.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.46,0:17:51.29,Default,Yoki,0000,0000,0000,,We can just take this path here, you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.29,0:17:53.76,Default,Zam,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, you're pretty amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.76,0:17:56.17,Default,Yoki,0000,0000,0000,,Keep the compliments coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.76,0:18:01.14,Default,Jer,0000,0000,0000,,With this, we should be able to reach the other side of the mountain a lot faster than we thought we would.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.18,0:18:08.64,Default,Zam,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Doctor Marcoh... Do you think those research documents hold anything to get us back to our old bodies?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.10,0:18:10.56,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,There is a possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.98,0:18:14.40,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,It's tough to say because it's not a form of alchemy we're familiar with.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.40,0:18:16.57,Default,Jer,0000,0000,0000,,I've got faith, Doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.57,0:18:19.61,Default,Jer,0000,0000,0000,,I really want to see my family!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.53,0:18:23.24,Default,Zam,0000,0000,0000,,Even though your wife was always leading you by the nose?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.24,0:18:26.04,Default,Zam,0000,0000,0000,,You probably only want to see your daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.04,0:18:31.58,Default,Jer,0000,0000,0000,,Look who's talking! You always turn nasty when you're drunk, so your son was just about fed up with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.58,0:18:33.88,Default,Jer,0000,0000,0000,,You still have the guts to see him now?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.88,0:18:35.71,Default,Zam,0000,0000,0000,,That was brutal.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.34,0:18:40.43,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,Is something wrong, May?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.84,0:18:41.72,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.01,0:18:48.18,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,I was just wondering when I'll be able to return, since my people are waiting for me...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.19,0:18:54.94,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,The philosopher's stone uses the lives of humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.27,0:18:58.19,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,I mustn't seek such a thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.74,0:19:01.53,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,Even if I tell him how to create one,\Nwithout bringing back an actual stone,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.53,0:19:04.91,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,the Emperor would make plans to create one without hesitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.54,0:19:08.58,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,By sacrificing the lives of many people...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.37,0:19:13.79,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,Immortality... Just what should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.79,0:19:19.05,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,That answer may also be hidden in those research documents.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.67,0:19:22.89,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,So let's try to get to the fort as quickly as we can to decipher them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.55,0:19:24.64,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.64,0:19:27.43,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,The fort is no longer safe?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.43,0:19:31.06,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Major General Armstrong has been summoned to Central.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.64,0:19:34.48,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Many soldiers from Central are now stationed at the fort, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.11,0:19:38.07,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Kimblee must have proposed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.07,0:19:42.24,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,He was making quite a few phone calls while at the fort, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.91,0:19:45.83,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Hang on. If the Major General is no longer there...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.28,0:19:50.08,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,An officer loyal to Bradley is going to be stationed there.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.08,0:19:51.87,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,So, Winry and the rest of them...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.87,0:19:54.42,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,It's going to be a lot more difficult to hide them there now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.71,0:19:57.88,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,That's hardly the issue. If things take a turn for the worse, they could fall in the hands of the enemy...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.13,0:20:04.64,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,We have to let them know somehow!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.64,0:20:08.14,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,It would be impossible to go after them in this blizzard.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.14,0:20:10.22,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,But we can't just leave them!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.22,0:20:11.52,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.52,0:20:14.23,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,An amateur shouldn't take a blizzard lightly!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.23,0:20:17.48,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,It'll suck out all your strength in a matter of minutes, leaving you to freeze to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.57,0:20:20.23,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,There's another option.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.44,0:20:27.41,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,There's someone here with a body that knows no fatigue and won't freeze.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.29,0:20:37.38,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,This is worse than I expected...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.79,0:20:41.21,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Now, where's the landmark...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.13,0:20:43.01,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,There!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.10,0:20:52.02,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I can't see anything with the snow blowing everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.00,0:21:21.50,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,What was that just now? My body?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.26,0:21:25.13,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.84,0:21:30.68,Default,66,0000,0000,0000,,It's impossible to place a soul on a body that doesn't belong. {ep19}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.89,0:21:35.35,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,A body that shouldn't possess a soul...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.73,0:21:36.94,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,A rejection reaction!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.23,0:21:42.15,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,My old body is pulling my soul towards it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.15,0:21:49.24,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Come on! Get it together!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.83,0:21:53.66,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I have to hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.58,0:22:01.04,Default,Father,0000,0000,0000,,Alphonse Elric.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.55,0:22:06.13,Default,Father,0000,0000,0000,,Edward Elric.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.51,0:22:09.68,Default,Father,0000,0000,0000,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.18,0:22:13.89,Default,Father,0000,0000,0000,,...Van Hohenheim.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.56,0:22:19.44,Default,Father,0000,0000,0000,,Izumi Curtis is also a possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.73,0:22:25.53,Default,Father,0000,0000,0000,,Just one more.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.08,0:24:00.45,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,A departure toward an unknown world.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.45,0:24:03.92,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,It's due to one's heart seeking something new.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.42,0:24:07.71,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,A human can never go against the wishes of his heart,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.71,0:24:11.51,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,but conflict always arises in that moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.30,0:24:16.72,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, Fullmetal Alchemist:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.72,0:24:19.60,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 40, Homunculus.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.22,0:24:22.69,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,The righteous isn't the one to win.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.69,0:24:25.94,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,The one to overcome the boundaries shall stand as the winner.
